- **GreatReads Integration** (external reading tracker at `GREATREADS_URL`, default `http://100.69.184.113:8007`)
  - **Overview**: GreatReads is a separate Django-based reading tracker application. Code lives at `../GreatReads/`. **CRITICAL**: When working with GreatReads integration, ALWAYS check the actual GreatReads codebase/database schema — never guess about field names, data structures, or API behavior.
  - **Chain Structure**: GreatReads uses a **linked-list chain** per media format. Each `read` record has an `id_previous` field pointing to the previous reading in that format's chain. The NEXT book in the chain is the one whose `id_previous` points to the CURRENT reading. See `../GreatReads/CHAIN_SYSTEM_ANALYSIS.md` for full details.
  - **Key GreatReads Fields** (from `../GreatReads/src/greatreads.db` schema):
    - `id` — reading ID
    - `id_previous` — FK to `read.id`, creates the chain structure (null = chain head)
    - `book_id` — FK to the book
    - `media` — format string: "Physical", "Ebook", "Audio"
    - `status` — reading status (in GreatReads, typically "finished" or inferred from dates)
    - `date_started` — actual start date
    - `date_finished_actual` — actual finish date
    - `date_est_start`, `date_est_end` — calculated by GreatReads' chain calculator
    - `rating_overall`, `rating_horror`, `rating_spice`, `rating_world_building`, `rating_writing`, `rating_characters`, `rating_readability`, `rating_enjoyment` — all floats, 0-10 scale
    - `rank` — separate ordering field (not used for chains)
  - `GET  /api/greatreads/format/<bookId>` — auto-detect the media format GreatReads is tracking for a book (Physical/Ebook/Audio). Queries GreatReads readings filtered by title, prioritizes in-progress, returns `{media, readingId, status}` or nulls when not found.
  - `POST /api/greatreads/finish` — mark a book as finished in GreatReads. Body: `{bookId, title, author, media, finishDate (YYYY-MM-DD), rating (0-10 overall), ratings: {horror, spice, world_building, writing, characters, readability, enjoyment (all 0-10)}, readingId: int | null (optional; the exact GreatReads reading to update — critical for re-reads)}`. Flow: (1) If `readingId` provided, fetch that reading directly; else search by title+media and prioritize in-progress. (2) **BEFORE marking current as finished**, find the next book in the chain by querying all readings for that media and finding the one whose `id_previous == current_reading_id`. (3) Update current reading to finished with ratings. (4) **START the next reading** by setting its `date_started` and `status` to `in_progress`. (5) Clear local progress for the finished book. (6) Return `{success, readingId, message, nextBook: {id, title, author, cover, mediaTypes}}` where nextBook is the one we just started in GreatReads.
